{"title": "With the Anzacs in Cairo", "description": "Guy Thornton recounts his experiences serving as a military chaplain with the Australian and New Zealand Army Corps (ANZAC) while stationed in Egypt during World War I.  His writing is opinionated, emotionally vulnerable, and written in very colorful, vivid prose. He recounts both his successes and failures as a pastor. Of particular concern to Thornton, are his soldiers\u2019 interactions with the Wasa'a- the red-light district of Cairo which was popular with the soldiers who often patronized prostitutes. Thornton also expresses his experiences exploring Cairo, his work as a chaplain, and the various social services catering to soldiers. \n - Summary by Adam Bielka", "duration": 10163, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "14738", "name": "Guy Thornton"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/anzacs_in_cairo_2003_librivox/with_anzacs_cairo_2003.jpg", "copyright_year": "1917", "genres": ["War & Military", "Memoirs"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Adam Bielka"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Adam Bielka"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Amy Gramour"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "KevinS"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Foreword", "readers": [13830], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/anzacs_in_cairo_2003_librivox/anzacsincairo_00_thornton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 220}, {"section": 1, "title": "Our Arrival at Zeitoun", "readers": [13830], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/anzacs_in_cairo_2003_librivox/anzacsincairo_01_thornton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 986}, {"section": 2, "title": "The City of Cairo", "readers": [13830], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/anzacs_in_cairo_2003_librivox/anzacsincairo_02_thornton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 729}, {"section": 3, "title": "The City of Cairo- continued", "readers": [13830], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/anzacs_in_cairo_2003_librivox/anzacsincairo_03_thornton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 880}, {"section